{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a65417cc3fb48d662b9", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 210, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9f"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "615d92ebde3d91842a5cf7e6", "title": "JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr Shift 2 Online)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "A copper rod of mass $\\mathrm{m}$ slides under gravity on two smooth parallel rails, with separation $l$ and set at an angle of $\\theta$ with the horizontal. At the bottom, rails are joined by a resistance R. There is a uniform magnetic field $\\mathrm{B}$ normal to the plane of the rails, as shown in the figure. The terminal speed of the copper rod is:\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/nPtk98OV8m_xU2gG5kncRd0J3LvljrdeUJRyRI0A220.original.fullsize.png\"><br>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "WNrm5", "text": "\n$\\frac{\\mathrm{mgR} \\cos \\theta}{\\mathrm{B}^2 l^2}$\n", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "2BwXe", "text": "\n$\\frac{\\mathrm{mgR} \\sin \\theta}{\\mathrm{B}^2 l^2}$\n", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "YnPLZ", "text": "\n$\\frac{\\mathrm{mgR} \\tan \\theta}{\\mathrm{B}^2 l^2}$\n", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "gmp5m", "text": "\n$\\frac{\\mathrm{mgR} \\cot \\theta}{\\mathrm{B}^2 l^2}$", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "From Faraday's law of electomagnetic induction,\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\ne &=\\frac{d \\phi}{d t}=\\frac{d(B A)}{l t}=\\frac{d(B l l)}{d t} \\\\\n&=\\frac{B d l \\times l}{d t}=B V l\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nAlso, $F=i l B=\\left(\\frac{B V}{R}\\right)\\left(l^2 B\\right)=\\frac{B^2 l^2 V}{R}$\nAt equilibrium\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/IThq93sgx3l5iFAgin_lVatWj22hs8CBE9bN-ro8ftM.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n$$\nm g \\sin \\theta=\\frac{B^2 l V}{R} \\Rightarrow V=\\frac{m g R \\sin \\theta}{B^2 l^2}\n$$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGJMPYQ52700136", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c2e8ce0dc8a5c62d2d", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352b", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7d", "616056cd0283de43c87e3e15", "616057190283de43c87e3e18", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd7", "64d50bd73df7f4a7f3017f6f", "66b79b34d4b564dfab4f94cc", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc11", "67fa5fef4468eb1307ceb0ad", "6807d2ad647479b8e8696479"], "cpyqbChapters": ["61602427cba2fa9ed9e72f82", "61bb82298adb7037e33f5e90", "6160242956b3f4e9b44d7836", "6160242ae6745f9dfbbf4eef", "61964c8f2c567a99ecc74113", "61602429b42b3007928c2021", "61e7bd7f4ea4ca4e8a493885", "6160242803cde39247fbcbae", "61964c8f782d0b7527c95ac9", "61c089b6c9a8a8e3433b1b2d", "6296212226b6eca689110f83", "629f390b0e3e15ddeed9a64e", "629109ebf9b127a2e6449c7b", "629f3a90c4d08c5950ee686b", "64eb06bf3118f713ecfef066", "66d58539a75f05ee8564f55f", "67921d671d5b5072da5e9ac6", "67fdff47378e1624ea7b6991", "6809202e3a10446a207fdf0c"], "cpyqbExams": ["615f0e999476412f48314daf", "616059af0283de43c87e3e23"]}}